            "title": "CAPENATURE VACANCIES",
            "content": [
                " \nCAPENATURE\n ",
                "LANDSCAPE ADMINISTRATOR ASSISTANT (LEVEL 5), HOTTENTOTS HOLLAND NATURE RESERVE\nCapeNature\nVilliersdorp, Western Cape\nPermanent\nAPPLY\n \nClosing Date 25 June 2024\n \nJob Details\nDivision: Conservation Operations\nBusiness Unit: Landscape West\nMinimum experience: Entry Level\nCompany primary industry: Environmental Services\nJob functional area: Operations\nSalary: R262 992 - R262 992 per annum\n \nJob Description\nThe purpose of this position will be to provide the required financial and administrative support to the Conservation Manager of the Hottentots Holland Nature Reserve.\n \nRESPONSIBILITIES:\n \nFinancial and Budget Management\nAssisting with administering budgets and externally funded projects\nAssist with Asset management, including Fixed Asset verifications, register management as well as purchase, disposal, and transfer management.\nManagement of Government Garage vehicle fleet, including logbooks, trip authorities, invoices, accruals, licensing, services, and repairs.\n \nOffice Administration & Management\nOffice administration including information management, minute taking at meetings, logistical aspects around meetings, workshops, and conferences.\nPrinting, scanning, and filing of documents- Document Management\nIncome and cash handling, including petty cash custodian, banking, and reconciliations.\nRender logistical and admin support at fires.\n \nSupply Chain Management\nManagement procurement of goods & services, including completion of purchase requests, receiving goods, arranging invoice approvals, and submission for payment\n \nReporting\nAssist with loss management including monthly reports.\nAssist with Consumable stock management, including monthly stock counts, reconciliations, and reporting\nProvide support to the Reserve Manager for reporting deadlines\n \nClient Liaison\nLiaising with internal and external customers\nOther administration duties as required and answering general inquiries.",
                "MINIMUM REQUIREMENTS \nQualifications and experience\nGrade 12 or Diploma/ Degree in Financial Management/Accounting.\n2 - 3 years\u2019 appropriate experience in Finance and or Administration.\nA valid driver\u2019s license.\nA good working knowledge of the MS Office suite particularly MS Outlook, MS. Word, and MS Excel.\nGood interpersonal and analytical skills.\nGood oral and written communication skills in in two official languages of the Western Cape.\nNo criminal record\n \nCompetencies\nStrong analytical, strategic, and creative problem-solving skills\nPeople skills and customer service-focused\nAbility to function independently and within a team.\nWillingness to travel\nUnderstanding of PFMA and related public sector supply chain processes\n \nRecommendation\nDiploma/ Degree in Financial Management/Accounting\n \nApply online at https://capenature.simplify.hr/\n \nClosing date: 25 June 2024\n \nAPPLY"
            ],
