                " \nWESTERN CAPE LIQUOR AUTHORITY (WCLA)\n ",
                "SENIOR MANAGER: LIQUOR LICENSING ADMINISTRATION \nComponent: Liquor Licensing Administration \nDepartment: Western Cape Liquor Authority (Bellville) \nReference Number: WCLA 04/2024 \n \nRequirements:\nBachelor\u2019s Degree (NQF 7) \nAt least 5-7 year\u2019s relevant experience (2-years\u2019 experience in a management capacity) \n \nExperience and competencies which will be considered to be advantageous: \nAdministrative experience relating to a compliance and quasi-judicial environment. \nProjects linked to the automation and digitization of systems and processes. \n \nKey performance areas: \n \nManagement of Component: \nIntroduce, maintain and implement LLA policies and procedures to administer applications in terms of the WCLA Act. \nParticipate in and contribute to the strategic decision-making processes of the WCLA. \nPrepare and manage budget for Component. \nProactively manage, report and account for the component\u2019s performance. \nDevelop, introduce and monitor SOP\u2019s (internal controls) for the component. \nEnsure good governance within the unit in line with the corporate governance guidelines and related legislation. \nEnsure effective identification and management of business risks, resources and continuous improvement within the unit. \nEnsure compliance of the component with all audit requirements emanating from audit processes within the component. \n \nLiquor License Application Management: \nOversee and manage the processing of all liquor licence applications as provided for in the Western Cape Liquor Act. \nOversee and manage the implementation and maintenance of the Licence Management and Tracking System (LMATS). \n \nRenewals Management: \nOversee and manage the processing of liquor licence renewals (automatic and non-automatic) of all valid licenses as provided for in the Western Cape Liquor Act. \nOversee and manage the administrative processes related to the non-automatic renewal of all valid licenses. \n \nClient Services Management: \nOversee and manage the walk-in centre (in-person, email, and telephonic client services). \nDrive process simplification, digitization and automation. \nOversee and manage the implementation and maintenance of the eLicence Portal (online application platform). \n \nResource and People Management: \nEstablish and maintain appropriate systems (analytical tools, information systems, projections of cost) and policies to ensure effective and efficient management of resources. \nPerform accurate forecasting, budgeting and allocation of resources within the unit. \nManage capacity within the unit to ensure sustained service delivery. \nBuild and foster a culture of good governance, customer service, honesty and integrity and world class delivery in the component. \n \nKnowledge:\nWorking knowledge of relevant Public Sector legislation, e.g., PFMA, National and Provincial Treasury Regulations, Administrative Law. \nHigh level of working knowledge of relevant industry legislation and regulations, e.g., National Liquor Act, Provincial Liquor Act, POPI, PAJA, PAIA. \nWorking knowledge of Risk Management and Project Management. \n \nSkills:\nHigh level of report writing skills \nExceptional interpersonal, communication, writing, reporting and presentation skills \nAbility to function independently and within a team \nAbility to prioritize and adapt, managing multiple projects and tight deadlines \nComputer literacy plus advanced proficiency in MS Office \n \n \nPlease Note: Only shortlisted applicants will receive further correspondence. If you have not received a response from the entity within three months of the closing date, please regard your application as unsuccessful. \n \nApplicants must submit a formal WCLA Application form, a comprehensive CV, certified copies of qualifications, identity document and driver\u2019s license (where applicable). Incomplete applications will not be considered. Applications must be submitted electronically preferably as one PDF document to hr@wcla.gov.za. \nWCLA Application forms can be obtained from the WCLA website: www.wcla.gov.za and must reach the Human Resources Section on or before the closing date indicated. Applicants must clearly state the reference number and position title in the subject line of the e-mail. Only Electronic applications will be accepted. \n \nPlease note that the following will lead to disqualification of applications: \nSubmission of fraudulent qualifications and / or documentation. \nNon-submission of certified copies of academic qualifications / records. \nNon-submission of WCLA Application form, CV, Identity document and Driver\u2019s License (where applicable). \n \nShortlisted candidates will be subjected to a vetting process. By applying for this position, candidates agree to reference checks, criminal and qualification checks being performed. \n \nThe WCLA reserves the right not to make an appointment. \n \nThe Western Cape Liquor Authority is guided by the principles of Employment Equity. All candidates invited for interviews may be subjected to competency test/practical tests as part of the interview process. Kindly note that all personal information provided with your application will be dealt with for the intended purpose. \n \nOnly applications submitted via the above-mentioned e-mail address will be accepted \n \nSALARY: R849 702 per annum (Cost to Employment) \nSALARY LEVEL: 11 \n \nCLOSING DATE: 21 June 2024 \n \nENQUIRIES: Mrs. S Langeveldt: (021) 204 9730 / 92",
                "HR BUSINESS PARTNER \nComponent: Corporate Services \nDepartment: Western Cape Liquor Authority (Bellville) \nReference Number: WCLA 05/2024\n \nRequirements:\nBachelor\u2019s Degree (NQF 7) in HR or Industrial Psychology \nAt least 4-6 year\u2019s relevant experience as a HRBP or HR Generalist \n \nExperience and competencies which will be considered to be advantageous: \nTwo (2) years supervisory experience. \nRegistration with a recognized professional body. \nSAGE 300 People HR and Payroll system. \n \nKey performance areas: \nTalent Attraction and Selection: \nFacilitate the implementation of the talent attraction and selection strategy. \nIdentify business unit skills and workforce needs. \nMaintain a comprehensive recruitment report and submit it to Line Manager for approval. \nProvide reporting/statistical analysis to the HR Manager on a quarterly/annual basis. \nTalent Management: \nFacilitate the implementation of talent retention strategies. \nFacilitate talent forum meetings. \nMonitor the development of the identified talent for readiness into the positions they are identified for. \nProvide reporting/statistical analysis to the HR Manager on a quarterly basis. \n \nLearning and Development:\nCoordinate Learning and Development. \nProvide support to learning and development programmes. \nFacilitate identification and development of Competency Development Programmes and Customised Interventions. \nTrain line management to conduct performance management, coach and mentor staff. \nManage a training resource database. \nProvide reporting/statistical analysis to the HR Manager on a quarterly basis. \n \nPerformance Management: \nFacilitate the implementation of performance management strategies. \nFacilitate the moderation process. \nManage performance management in accordance with policies, procedures and legal requirements \nProvide reporting/statistical analysis to the HR Manager on a quarterly basis. \n \nIndustrial Relations: \nAdvise and support Line Managers in effecting appropriate industrial relations processes. \nProactively manage employee relations matters before they escalate into grievances. \nManage and maintain employee relations information and documentation. \nProvide reporting/statistical analysis to the HR Manager on a quarterly basis. \n \nEmployee Wellness: \nCoordinate the employee wellness function of WCLA. \nLiaise with Employee Wellness Service Providers. \nProduce and present Employee Wellness reports, as required. \nProvide reporting/statistical analysis to the HR Manager on a quarterly basis. \n \nKnowledge and skills: \nA sound knowledge and functioning of government systems and applicable legislations and regulations \nGood communication skills, project management skills, presentation skills, report writing skills, planning, and organizing, problem solving and analysis skills. \nWorking knowledge of relevant HR legislation, e.g. BCEA, LRA, EEA, SDA, etc. \n \n \nPlease Note: Only shortlisted applicants will receive further correspondence. If you have not received a response from the entity within three months of the closing date, please regard your application as unsuccessful. \n\nApplicants must submit a formal WCLA Application form, a comprehensive CV, certified copies of qualifications, identity document and driver\u2019s license (where applicable). Incomplete applications will not be considered. Applications must be submitted electronically preferably as one PDF document to hr@wcla.gov.za. \nWCLA Application forms can be obtained from the WCLA website: www.wcla.gov.za and must reach the Human Resources Section on or before the closing date indicated. Applicants must clearly state the reference number and position title in the subject line of the e-mail. Only Electronic applications will be accepted. \n \nPlease note that the following will lead to disqualification of applications: \nSubmission of fraudulent qualifications and / or documentation. \nNon-submission of certified copies of academic qualifications / records. \nNon-submission of WCLA Application form, CV, Identity document and Driver\u2019s License (where applicable). \n \nShortlisted candidates will be subjected to a vetting process. By applying for this position, candidates agree to reference checks, criminal and qualification checks being performed. \n \nThe WCLA reserves the right not to make an appointment. \n \nThe Western Cape Liquor Authority is guided by the principles of Employment Equity. All candidates invited for interviews may be subjected to competency test/practical tests as part of the interview process. Kindly note that all personal information provided with your application will be dealt with for the intended purpose. \n \nOnly applications submitted via the above-mentioned e-mail address will be accepted \n \nSALARY: R515 686 per annum (Cost to Employment) \nSALARY LEVEL: 8\n \nCLOSING DATE: 21 June 2024 \n \nENQUIRIES: Mrs. S Langeveldt: (021) 204 9730 / 92"
