                " \nRAND WATER\n ",
                " \n \n \nRE-ADVERTISEMENT- CONSULTANT AUTOMATION ENGINEER/TECHNOLOGIST\n \nDetails\nRe-Advertisement- Consultant Automation Engineer/Technologist (RAN240612-1) - Rand Water\nClosing Date 2024/06/25\nReference Number RAN240612-1\nJob Title Re-Advertisement- Consultant Automation Engineer/Technologist\nPortfolio Strategy\nJob Type Classification Permanent\nLocation \u2013 Country South Africa\nLocation \u2013 Province Gauteng\nLocation - Town / City Glenvista\nLocation \u2013 Site Rietvlei\n \nJob Advert Summary\nTo assist the Automation Asset Manager to act as the custodian for automation plants and sub-plants of the water supply infrastructure. This individual is responsible for ensuring that these assets are specified, installed, operated, and maintained to provide expected levels of service at minimum lifecycle cost.\n \nMinimum Requirements\nEssential (must-have) qualifications are:\n\u2022 Formal engineering qualifications (MTech, MEng, MScEng degree)\n\u2022 Professional Registration with the Engineering Council of SA\n\u2022 6 to 10 years\u2019 experience in industrial automation (measurement, control and instrumentation)engineering / infrastructure management\n\u2022 Minimum of 3 years\u2019 management experience\n \nDesirable qualifications are:\n\u2022 Advanced Management Programme\n\u2022 Membership of a fraternal voluntary association\n \nPrimary Duties\n\u2022 Assist the Automation Asset Manager to lead and manage all activities of the section that will result in optimal lifecycle performance of the specific category of assets\n\u2022 Assist the Automation Asset Manager to develop, compile, execute and manage the section business plan that supports the departmental and divisional business plan\n\u2022 Assist the Automation Asset Manager to develop and maintain generic standards for asset performance and availability, maintenance regimes, rates of deterioration, lifespan, etc.\n\u2022 Provide and update plans and costs for the management of each asset, for incorporation into the integrated Asset Management Plan\n\u2022 Manage and lead the process relating to the review and improvement of standards and specifications for the asset category\n\u2022 Manage asset assessors and maintenance staff in:\nCondition assessment and performance measurement of assets to agreed standards and frequencies\nRegular audits of maintenance activities\nProviding a maintenance support service to operating sites\n\u2022 Manage, specify and review improvements to design specifications, operating and maintenance regimes.\n\u2022 Review and approve specification and design of new assets to ensure lifecycle performance is adequately addressed\n\u2022 Develop and prepare annual budget for Automation asset management, and practice financial management and control\n\u2022 Assist the Automation Asset Manager to manage the development of staff by monitoring performance, coaching and mentoring, career path and succession planning\n\n\u2022 Initiate and lead Automation asset management related projects\n\u2022 Direct and lead technical advances and world class expertise for the category of asset\n\u2022 People and resource management by monitoring performance of staff and implement succession planning\n\u2022 Effective management and monitoring the section\u2019s budget to ensure actual expenses against budgeted amount and delegate action on variances\n\u2022 Create and encourage a culture of teamwork, and achievement, through the application of frequent feedback and communication with staff and promote employment equity\n \nKnowledge\n\u2022 Specification, design, operation, and maintenance of the asset category (i.e., automation engineering)\n\u2022 Financial and economic principles, including life cycle costing\n\u2022 Condition assessment and performance measurement techniques and evaluation\n\u2022 Asset rehabilitation technology\n\u2022 Principles of plant maintenance and reliability\n\u2022 Principles of asset management\n \nSkills\n\u2022 Technical report writing and development of specifications\n\u2022 SCADA and HMI installation and commissioning\n\u2022 PLC programming and configuration, I/O installation, and commissioning\n\u2022 Installation and wiring of instruments to the PLC and control panel I/Os\n\u2022 Electrical control panel construction, installation and commissioning\n\u2022 Control panel fault tracing, redesign, and re-wiring\n\u2022 System alarm reporting and logging\n\u2022 Industrial networking and telemetry systems\n\u2022 Production of P&ID and AsBuilt drawings \n \nAttitude         \n\u2022 Customer service\n\u2022 Critical evaluation\n\u2022 Decision making\n\u2022 Planning and organizing\n\u2022 Effective communication and interpersonal skills\n\u2022 People management\n\u2022 Self-management\n\u2022 Conceptual thought and well developed analytical and coordinating skills\n\u2022 Problem solving\n\u2022 Project management planning principles, tools and techniques\n\u2022 Networking skills\n\u2022 Spatial analysis and interpretation \n \n \nPolicy\nWe are committed to Employment Equity when recruiting internally and externally. In evaluating prospective applicants and making the final selection, preference will be given to females and/ or people with disabilities to give effect to Rand Water's Employment Equity objectives.\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE\n \n \n \n ",
                "WORKSHOP AIDE\n \nDetails\nWorkshop Aide (RAN240605-1) - Rand Water\nClosing Date 2024/06/18\nReference Number RAN240605-1\nJob Title Workshop Aide\nPortfolio Bulk Water Services - Operations\nJob Type Classification Permanent\nLocation \u2013 Country South Africa\nLocation \u2013 Province Gauteng\nLocation - Town / City Johannesburg South\nLocation - Site Central Depot / Bulk Distribution\n \nJob Advert Summary\nRand Water is looking for a candidate who will be responsible for maintaining a clean and safe workshop at all times.\n \nMinimum Requirements       \nGrade 12.\n2 years relevant workshop environment.\nBasic SHE knowledge.\n \nPrimary Duties\nPerform general housekeeping chores in and around the workshop.\nEnsuring that all workshop machinery and equipment are kept clean and in good working condition.\nMaintaining and cleaning waste bins.\n \nKnowledge    \nGeneral housekeeping.\nSafety knowledge.\nKnowledge of basic concepts relevant to the job.\n \nSkills\nAbility to keep all the waste area clean by sweeping with a broom.\ncollect all papers and unwanted items on the ground.\ncommunication skills.\n \nAttitude\nPerformance driven.\nTeam work .\nCustomer service orientation.\n \n \nPolicy\nWe are committed to Employment Equity when recruiting internally and externally. In evaluating prospective applicants and making the final selection, preference will be given to females and/ or people with disabilities to give effect to Rand Water's Employment Equity objectives.\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE",
                "ENVIRONMENTAL ADVISOR\n \nDetails\nClosing Date 2024/06/14\nReference Number RAN240603-1\nJob Title ENVIRONMENTAL ADVISOR\nPortfolio Shared Services\nJob Type Classification Permanent\nLocation \u2013 Country South Africa\nLocation \u2013 Province Gauteng\nLocation - Town / City Johannesburg\nLocation \u2013 Site Rietvlei\n \nJob Advert Summary\nTo develop and maintain a corporate environmental and occupational hygiene system, establish systems to mitigate all associated risks identified within the organisation and provide advice to management and operating sites to ensure alignment with best practise.\n \nMinimum Requirements\nMatric qualification is essential\nBtech Degree in Environmental Health Management or equivalent\nAccredited Advanced SHE Auditor would be an advantage (14001, 18001 and 9001)\n3 - 5 years experience Environmental Management or 2 years at a supervisory or managerial level\nKnowledge of 14000 is essential\nUnderstand the business area (activities, process, sources of emissions)\nUnderstand accountabilities and roles in business areas + developed \u2018customer\u2019 network\nUnderstand/identify environmental hazards associated with the business\nKnow key sensitivities in baseline environment\nGood understanding of the Water Services act and other applicable environmental legislation.\nExperience of EMS implementation and water sector\nMust be computer literate in MS Office Suite, word processing and database\nCode 8 drivers licence.\n \nPrimary Duties\nAssist the sites in implementing processes to ensure construction works are conducted in accordance with environmental legislation and Corporate environmental standards.\nAdvice the sites on current and applicable environmental legislation and industry best practice\nProvide detailed environmental support and guidance in the planning stages of a new projects.\nEnsure environmental audits are conducted to ensure compliance against legislative and corporate environmental standards.\nProvide support and guidance in establishing site specific environmental objectives, which are commensurate with Corporate environmental objectives, which provide practical solutions to environmental concerns.\nLiaise with external regulatory bodies ( GDACE, DEAT etc.) in the management of environmental incidents.\nAttend relevant environmental industry / regulatory associations / forums so as to assist in the improvement of overall environmental performance.\nProvide relevant information for Environmental Management reviews.\nVisit Rand Water sites and provide support to the Risk Control teams.\nPro-active assistance on Occupation Health, Safety and environmental matters.\nImplement and maintain an occupational hygiene programme for all Rand Water operations.\nDraft Group Policies and Procedures/ Guidelines\nAssists sites in implementation and maintaining ISO 14001& OHSAS 18001\nCompile comprehensive reports on environmental performance.\nAssists in conducting aspects and impacts assessments.\nSupport to initial / small projects, including advice & input on permits/legal requirements/ impact assessments\nMaintain the Corporate SHE Compliance manual\n \nKnowledge\nRelated Environmental Legislation\nSafety and Environmental issues\nStatistics\nRisk Management\nComputer literacy (word processing and database)\nEnvironmental Audits\nBudget Management\n \nSkills\nStrong Communication Skills (verbal and written).\nGood Interpersonal skills\nInterviewing skills.\nDecision making\nReport writing skills\n \nAttitude\nAssertiveness\nLogical thinker\nAbility to work independently and under pressure\nAbility to pay attention to detail\nDecisiveness\nDeadline oriented and able to deliver good quality outputs within short timeframes\n \n \nPolicy\nWe are committed to Employment Equity when recruiting internally and externally. In evaluating prospective applicants and making the final selection, preference will be given to females and/ or people with disabilities to give effect to Rand Water's Employment Equity objectives.\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE"
